description: Rapid OPC client and subscriber development. Supports OPC Data Access, XML-DA, Alarms&Events and Unified Architecture (OPC UA), including PubSub. Allows procedural coding, live binding (code-less development), live mapping, and reactive programming models. Works with .NET Framework and .NET 6+ on Microsoft Windows, Linux and macOS.
releaseNotes: Table of all versions, with their basic requirements, and links to "What's New" pages: https://kb.opclabs.com/QuickOPC_Versions .
title: QuickOPC Client and Subscriber Toolkit for OPC UA and OPC Classic
